oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Webster Memorial Baptist Church, 2002 January
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photograph of Webster Memorial Baptist Church located at 816 W Greenwood Avenue in Nashville, Tennessee. The foundation is stone. The exterior walls are made of concrete blocks that have been painted white. The front facade has some vertical wood siding. The roof is gabled with tar shingles. The windows are square with clear glass. The doors are wooden. Forms part of the Historic Nashville, Inc. Sacred Sites Survey Project. 1 photograph : col. ; 4 x 6 in.
